de.unistuttgart.vis.wearable.os.api

Class CallbackFlags

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.unistuttgart.vis.wearable.os.api.CallbackFlags

  • public final class CallbackFlags
extends java.lang.Object

    As provided by the APIFunctions.registerCallback(IGarmentCallback, int) the developer has the ability to register for several different events that are recognized during the runtime of the GarmentOS Service.

    This class provides the flags for these events the developer can register for and will get call backed by the service. As the developer wishes, we can register for none, one or multiple events, depending on his needs.
    Multiple flags can be provided by either calling the multipleCallbacks(int...) function or just putting them togehter using the binary or operator.
    Registering for NONE has the same effect as unregistering for all or all registered flags

    • NONE - register for none or unregister for all callbacks, no further callback will be made
    • SENSOR_ADDED - register for a callback if a new sensor has been added to the device
    • SENSOR_REMOVED - register for a callback if a new sensor has been removed from the device
    • GESTURE_PERFORMED - register for a callback if a gesture has been recognized
    • STEP_MADE - register for a callback if a step has been made
    • PRESSURE_DETECTED - register for a callback if a pressure event has been detected
    • ACTIVITY_CHANGED - register for a callback if the activity has changed
    • EMOTION_CHANGED - register for a callback if the emotion has changed
    • BODY_TEMPERATURE_CHANGED - register for a callback if the body temperature has changed
    • HEART_RATE_CHANGED - register for a callback if the heart rate has changed
    • PULSE_CHANGED - register for a callback if the pulse has changed
    • SKINCONDUCTANCE_CHANGED - register for a callback if the skin conductance has changed

    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    roehrdor

    • Method Detail

      • multipleCallbacks

        public static int multipleCallbacks(int... flags)

        Create a single flag value from multiple single flags. This function can be used since APIFunctions.registerCallback(IGarmentCallback, int) needs to be called with a single flag value. Instead of calling this function multiple times the developer can call this function to put multiple flags together.

        This function puts the binary or values together

        Parameters:
        flags - the flags that shall be put into a single flag value
        Returns:
        the single flag value for all the given flags
